Currently, these plants continue to supply their products both to AvtoVAZ and other Russian auto plants. AvtoVAZ, together with General Motors and the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, took part in the creation of a joint venture GM-AVTOVAZ. production began with the production of the Chevrolet Niva SUV (“Chevrolet Niva”). In 2019, AvtoVAZ launched the production of the Lada Largrus CNG powered by gas and gasoline. Thus, the AvtoVAZ line will be replenished with two biofuel models.[60]

On April 8, 1986, M. S. Gorbachev visited Togliatti, where the General Secretary of the CPSU Central Committee visited the automobile plant.